{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17506409","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17506409"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:42:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:42:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2536"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2536","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2536"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.78,0.09,0.02,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2536"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104435"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2536","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2536"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2536"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86762"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"38"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2166"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"3029"},{"type":"tags","id":"4342"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5420"},{"type":"tags","id":"5421"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2438"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2440"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27082"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27090"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29938"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31794"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38764"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104435","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/104435"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 29-year-old woman presents for her 36-week antenatal check-up. She recently moved to the area with her partner of two years after he accepted a new job. She has a university degree but stopped working full-time to prepare for the baby. During a private conversation, she discloses that her partner has become increasingly controlling, prevents her from seeing friends or family, and monitors her spending. She becomes tearful and expresses fear for her safety and that of her unborn baby. Her only social contact outside the home is at her part-time job three days per week.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following features should most strongly prompt screening for domestic violence in this case?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Recent job loss","Pregnancy","Socioeconomic status","Relationship duration","Educational level"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPregnancy\u003C/strong\u003E is a crucial time when all patients should be screened for domestic violence, as it represents a period of increased risk and vulnerability. Regular antenatal visits provide important opportunities for healthcare providers to screen and intervene.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are less reliable indicators for when to screen:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecent job loss\u003C/strong\u003E - While financial stress can contribute to domestic violence, all patients should be screened regardless of employment status\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESocioeconomic status\u003C/strong\u003E - Domestic violence occurs across all socioeconomic groups\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERelationship duration\u003C/strong\u003E - Violence can occur at any stage of a relationship\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEducational level\u003C/strong\u003E - Domestic violence affects people of all educational backgrounds\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers should screen all pregnant patients for domestic violence in a private setting, separate from their partner, and be prepared to provide appropriate support and referrals when disclosure occurs.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pregnancy is a high-risk period that requires routine screening for domestic violence during antenatal care.","Key warning signs for domestic violence include controlling behaviour, social isolation, and expressions of fear for safety.","Healthcare providers must screen for domestic violence in private settings and be prepared to offer appropriate support and referrals."],"references":["CDC contributors. Risk and Protective factors.  Centres for disease control and prevention. 2024 Feb. [Internet]. Accessed on 2025 Jan 13. Available from: https://www.cdc.gov/intimate-partner-violence/risk-factors/?CDC_AAref_Val=https://www.cdc.gov/violenceprevention/intimatepartnerviolence/riskprotectivefactors.html","Capaldi DM, Knoble NB, Shortt JW, Kim HK. A Systematic Review of Risk Factors for Intimate Partner Violence. Partner Abuse. 2012 Apr;3(2):231-280. doi: 10.1891/1946-6560.3.2.231. PMID: 22754606; PMCID: PMC3384540. Avaialble from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22754606/","Brownridge DA, Taillieu TL, Tyler KA, Tiwari A, Ko Ling Chan, Santos SC. Pregnancy and intimate partner violence: risk factors, severity, and health effects. Violence Against Women. 2011 Jul;17(7):858-81. doi: 10.1177/1077801211412547. PMID: 21775311. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21775311/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86762"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2536"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86762","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/86762"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-02T08:49:58+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-02T08:50:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2536"}},"co